Context: The George Brown College has a Strategic and Operational Planning Team that uses data and resources to guide strategic thinking and decision making in collaboration with colleagues across the college. They have released a new business plan for the 2022-2023 academic year, which includes initiatives to enhance digitization and next-generation teaching methods in response to COVID-19. The business plan aligns with the college's values, mindset and impact, vision for 2030, and commitments and priorities articulated in Strategy 2022. For more information about the business plan, please contact Dijana Praskac at dijana.praskac@georgebrown.ca or sign up to receive college news and updates. Additional contacts for the college are 416-415-2000 and TTY: 1-877-515-5559, with email inquiries going to ask.george@georgebrown.ca. The information on the website is subject to change without notice and should not be considered a representation or warranty. Students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements.
